{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"language":"python","display_name":"Python 3","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.12.12","mimetype":"text/x-python","codemirror_mode":{"name":"ipython","version":3},"pygments_lexer":"ipython3","nbconvert_exporter":"python","file_extension":".py"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[{"sourceType":"datasetVersion","sourceId":15288615,"datasetId":9779634,"databundleVersionId":16191115}],"dockerImageVersionId":31328,"isInternetEnabled":true,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"source":"<a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/code/ibrahimatefm/war-impact-oil-eda-modeling?scriptVersionId=307333275\" target=\"_blank\"><img align=\"left\" alt=\"Kaggle\" title=\"Open in Kaggle\" src=\"https://kaggle.com/static/images/open-in-kaggle.svg\"></a>","metadata":{},"cell_type":"markdown"},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# The Impact of the Iran-Israel Conflict on Oil Markets\nOil markets are among the most sensitive systems to geopolitical disruptions, particularly in regions that play a critical role in global energy supply. One of the most strategically important areas is the Strait of Hormuz, a narrow maritime corridor through which roughly 20% of the world's oil supply is transported daily.\n\nIn this notebook, we analyze the impact of the Iran War of 2026 on oil markets. We specifically focus on the escalation triggered by the US-Israel joint airstrikes on Iranian nuclear sites on February 28, 2026, and the subsequent systemic shocks to the global economy.\n\nThe analysis covers 25 trading days (Feb 9 – Mar 20, 2026) and explores how this supply shock propagated across global energy pricing systems.\nKey Events Timeline:\n\n    Feb 28, 2026: US-Israel joint airstrikes on Iranian nuclear sites.\n\n    Post-Strike: Announcement of the death of Supreme Leader Khamenei.\n\n    Immediate IRGC Response: Total closure of the Strait of Hormuz.\n\n    ⚠️ Note: This supply shock represents one of the most significant disruptions in modern energy history, leading to immediate \"Strait-specific\" premiums in pricing.\n\n## Analysis Objectives\n\nWe investigate the effect on major global oil benchmarks and secondary market indicators:\n### Primary Oil Benchmarks\n\n    Brent Crude: The global international benchmark.\n\n    WTI (West Texas Intermediate): The primary US benchmark.\n\n\n### Key Metrics & Correlations\n\n    Shipping Traffic Collapse: Tracking the halt of tanker movement through Hormuz.\n\n    Volatility Shifts: Analyzing intraday swings and \"limit-up\" trading sessions.\n\n\n### Special Focus To IRAN\n\n## Predictive Modeling: Approach\n\nTo move beyond historical analysis, we implement a framework to forecast critical market shifts. This allows us to quantify the expected impact.\n\nfocusing predictive modeling on the three most sensitive variables:\n\n- WTI & Brent Price Trajectory:\n\n       Daily closing price for the next 5 trading days.\n\n            -Lagged prices, Strait of Hormuz tanker throughput (volume), and USD Index (DXY) strength.\n\n- State-Level Gasoline Surge (e.g., California):\n\n        Average pump price per gallon.\n\n            - Crude oil spot prices (Brent/WTI) with a 3-day time lag, and regional inventory levels.\n\n---\n","metadata":{"_uuid":"8f2839f25d086af736a60e9eeb907d3b93b6e0e5","_cell_guid":"b1076dfc-b9ad-4769-8c92-a6c4dae69d19"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Setup","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"!pip install adjustText -q","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-29T04:10:51.331674Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-29T04:10:51.332035Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-29T04:10:55.490075Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-29T04:10:51.331992Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-29T04:10:55.488565Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"import pandas as pd\nimport numpy as np\nimport matplotlib.p