# Counterfactual scenarios\noil['revenue_at_full_production'] = prewar_prod * oil['brent']  # If production stayed constant\noil['revenue_at_prewar_prices'] = oil['iran_prod'] * prewar_brent  # If prices stayed constant\n\n# Decompose revenue effects\noil['price_premium_effect'] = oil['iran_prod'] * (oil['brent'] - prewar_brent)\noil['production_loss_effect'] = (oil['iran_prod'] - prewar_prod) * prewar_brent\noil['net_effect'] = oil['iran_revenue_m'] - prewar_revenue","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-29T04:10:55.576202Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-29T04:10:55.576482Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-29T04:10:55.605917Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-29T04:10:55.576457Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-29T04:10:55.604954Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# How Events Would Shockingly impact The market\n**Major Events**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(12, 10), sharex=True, gridspec_kw={'height_ratios': [2, 1]})\n\n# --- TOP PANEL: Oil Benchmark Reaction ---\nax1.plot(oil['date'], oil['brent'], color=OIL['brent'], linewidth=3, label='Brent Crude')\nax1.plot(oil['date'], oil['wti'], color=OIL['wti'], linewidth=2.5, label='WTI')\nax1.set_ylabel('Price (USD/Barrel)', fontweight='bold', fontsize=12)\nax1.set_title('Global Benchmark Price Explosion', color=OIL['subtitle'], loc='left', pad=10, fontsize=14)\nax1.legend(loc='upper left', frameon=False)\nax1.grid(True)\n\n# Marker: Conflict Day\nwar_start = pd.to_datetime('2026-02-28')\nwar_price = oil[oil['date'] == war_start]['brent'].values[0]\nax1.scatter(war_start, war_price, color=OIL['strike'], s=120, zorder=5, edgecolor=OIL['bg'])\nax1.text(war_start, war_price + 2, 'Conflict Start\\nHormuz Closure', \n         color=OIL['strike'], fontweight='bold', ha='right', fontsize=10)\n\n# --- BOTTOM PANEL: Hormuz Traffic Volume ---\nax2.bar(oil['date'], oil['hormuz_ships'], color=OIL['text_muted'], alpha=0.6, width=0.8, label='Hormuz Traffic')\nax2.set_ylabel('Daily Ship Count', fontweight='bold', fontsize=12)\nax2.set_title('Strait of Hormuz Traffic Collapse', color=OIL['subtitle'], loc='left', pad=10, fontsize=14)\nax2.grid(True, axis='y')\n\n# Subtle vertical synchronization line across both panels\nax1.axvline(war_start, color=OIL['strike'], linestyle=':', alpha=0.6)\nax2.axvline(war_start, color=OIL['strike'], linestyle=':', alpha=0.6)\n\nplt.suptitle('Supply Chain & Price Shock', color=OIL['title'], fontsize=18, fontweight='bold', y=0.98)\nplt.tight_layout(rect=[0, 0.05, 1, 0.98])\nplt.savefig('fracture_vs_spike.png')","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-29T04:10:55.607063Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-29T04:10:55.607496Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-29T04:10:56.473501Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-29T04:10:55.607457Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-29T04:10:56.472541Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## The Huge Effect of closing Strait of Hormuz\nThe ship count didn't just decline; it hit a functional zero.\n\nThis is a Supply Shock. ['hormuz_ships'] will likely be The strongest negative correlator—as ships go to 0, prices head toward the moon.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"corr_ships_brent = oil[['hormuz_ships', 'brent']].corr().iloc[0, 1]\n\n# (Standard Deviation)\npre_vol  = oil[oil['war_day'] < 0]['brent'].std()\npost_vol = oil[oil['war_day'] >= 1]['brent'].std()\n\n# (Z-Score)\npre_mean = oil[oil['war_day'] < 0]['brent'].mean()\npeak_price = oil['brent'].max()\nz_score = (peak_price - pre_mean) / pre_vol\n\nprint(f\"Ship/Price Correlation: {corr_ships_brent:.2f}\")\nprint(f\"Volatility Multiplier:  {post_vol / pre_vol:.1f}x\")\nprint(f\"Peak Price Z-Score:     {z_score:.1f}\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-29T04:10:56.474507Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-29T04:10:56.47476Z","iopub.status.