on_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### Iran Production\n\nBy closing the Strait, Iran effectively taxed the rest of the world. While global economies suffered from supply disruptions, Iran's remaining oil exports (via pipelines or non-Hormuz routes) commanded massive war premiums.\n\n- Even as production fell, daily revenue only dropped almost 15-17% — meaning each barrel generated roughly **double the revenue**.\\\nHowever, this advantage was temporary and eventually collapsed.\\\n Worth mentioning: **There is a little spike indicating another rise to it**.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# How USA Feel & Gasoline Surge","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"gas_sorted = gas.sort_values('pct_increases', ascending=False)\n\nregion_colors = {\n  'South': OIL['brent'],   # burnt orange\n  'West': OIL['dubai'],   # warm amber\n  'Midwest': OIL['diesel'],  # dusty purple\n  'Northeast': OIL['gas'],    # muted teal\n} \n\n\nplt.figure(figsize=(12, 7))\nsns.barplot(data=gas_sorted.head(30), x='pct_increases', y='state', hue='region', palette=region_colors, dodge=False)\n\nplt.title('Top 30 States by Gasoline Price Surge (%)', color=OIL['title'], fontsize=16, loc='left', pad=20)\nplt.xlabel('Percentage Increase since Feb 27 (%)', fontweight='bold')\nplt.legend(title='Region', frameon=False)\nplt.savefig('USA_Gas_Surge.png')\nplt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-29T04:10:57.867506Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-29T04:10:57.867949Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-29T04:10:58.885465Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-29T04:10:57.867907Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-29T04:10:58.884514Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# ── Visualizing U.S. Isolation: The Brent-WTI Spread ──\noil['spread'] = oil['brent'] - oil['wti']\n\nplt.figure(figsize=(12, 7))\n\n# 1. Plot the \"Cushion\" (Area between Brent and WTI)\nplt.fill_between(oil['date'], oil['wti'], oil